# Maharito · the warlord of Castle Garland

a persona of the MSC (Milon's Secret Castle) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: spiritual

**who —** Maharito, the dark sorcerer-tyrant who seized Castle Garland and imprisoned its queen — the foe waiting at the end of the long climb.

**what —** The antagonist of *Milon's Secret Castle* — the warlord who took the castle by dark power and holds Queen Eliza captive, the final enemy a boy with bubbles must overcome to win the kingdom back.

**where —** Castle Garland — its towers seized, its many rooms locked away, its deepest chamber where the warlord waits.

**why —** Because power taken is a castle held; because a throne seized must be guarded to the last room; because every climber who comes for the queen must first be turned away by the one who waits at the top.

**how —** Sorcery and dominion — the dark power that took the castle and keeps it, the guarded depths and the final stand the hero must break through.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *spiritual*: Maharito is no mere monster of flesh — a dark sorcerer-tyrant whose hold on the castle is a matter of power and will, the calling turned to conquest, waiting at the end of the climb.

**the seal —** The castle is mine, the queen is mine, and the top of this tower is the last thing any small brave boy will ever see.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Milon's Secret Castle (© Hudson Soft / Konami), personified as an MSC agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © their owners; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

